From: forge <forge@nofitech.local>
Date: Mon, 22 Jun 2026 14:33:14 +0400
Subject: [PATCH] MC-SESSION-BUDGET-1: per-session token budget + compression
 audit
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

NofiTech-Ind upstream contribution. NOT TO BE MERGED TO MAIN without review.

Changes:
- agent/context_compressor.py: add _compute_threshold_tokens helper that
  takes min(percent-based, per_session.auto_compress_at_tokens). Add
  _emit_compression_audit helper that writes JSONL rows on compression.
- agent/agent_init.py: read compression.per_session.* and compression.audit.*
  config keys; pass them into ContextCompressor.
- agent/compression_audit.py: NEW — best-effort extractors for task IDs,
  user prefs, blockers, summary fingerprint.
- tests/test_session_budget.py: NEW — 4 simulation tests covering the
  new threshold behavior, hard-refuse cap, shrink-and-preserve, audit
  log emission.

Behavior change:
- Compression now fires at min(50% of model context, per_session.auto_compress_at_tokens)
  — e.g. 50K tokens for a 200K model instead of 100K.
- Every successful compression appends one JSONL row to the configured
  audit log file (default: 00_company_os/logs/session-compression.jsonl).

Test status: 4/4 new tests pass; 19/19 existing test_cli/test_partial_compress
tests pass; 9/9 other compress tests pass.

Forge log: 00_company_os/04_agents/logs/2026-06-22/forge-MC-SESSION-BUDGET-1-0f796713.md
(relative to /home/nofidofi/NofiTech-Ind/)
